<div class=3D"wrapper"> <h1 id=3D"page-title" class=3D"page__title" itemprop=3D"headline"> =20 3DS Hacks Guide =20 </h1> =20 <p class=3D"page__lead">A complete guide to 3DS custom firmware, <b= r> from stock to boot9strap.<br> </p> =20 =20 =20 =20 </div> =20 =20 </div> <div id=3D"main" role=3D"main"> <article class=3D"splash" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/C= reativeWork"> <meta itemprop=3D"headline" content=3D"3DS Hacks Guide"> <meta itemprop=3D"description" content=3D"A complete guide to 3DS custo= m firmware, from stock to boot9strap."> =20 =20 <section class=3D"page__content" itemprop=3D"text"> <hr> =20 =20 =20 =20 <div class=3D"notice"><b>For support in English, ask for help at <a= href=3D"https://discord.gg/MWxPgEp" target=3D"_blank">Nintendo Homebrew on= Discord</a>.</b></div> =20 =20 <div class=3D"notice"><b>If you appreciate this guide, we accept <a= href=3D"https://3ds.hacks.guide/contribute#donations">Donations</a>.</b></= div> =20 <hr> =20 <div class=3D"notice--warning"> <p><strong>3DS firmware 11.16.0 was recently released</strong>. Here=E2=80= =99s what you should know:</p> <ul> <li>If your device is running <em>Luma 11.0</em>, it is <em>100% safe</em= > to update. You can check your Luma version by holding (Select) while boot= ing your device.</li> <li>If your device is on an older Luma version, you should <a href=3D"htt= ps://3ds.hacks.guide/checking-for-cfw">update Luma</a> before you update yo= ur device to 11.16.0.</li> <li>If your device does not yet have custom firmware, you can still insta= ll it on this version for free without any additional hardware, but the rec= ommended method has been changed.</li> </ul> </div> <p class=3D"notice--info">Thoroughly read all of the introductory pages (in= cluding this one!) before proceeding.</p> <h2 id=3D"what-is-custom-firmware">What is custom firmware?<a class=3D"head= er-link" href=3D"https://3ds.hacks.guide/#what-is-custom-firmware" title=3D= "Permalink"><span class=3D"sr-only">Permalink</span><i class=3D"fas fa-link= "></i></a></h2> <p><strong>Custom firmware</strong> (=E2=80=9CCFW=E2=80=9D) is a full softw= are modification to your 3DS, comparable to =E2=80=9Cadministrator access= =E2=80=9D on a computer. It allows you to do anything that the 3DS is physi= cally capable of doing, rather than being limited by whatever Nintendo allo= ws you to do.</p> <p>Popular uses for custom firmware include:</p> <ul> <li>Running homebrew software and games made for or ported to the Nintend= o 3DS</li> <li>Bypassing the region lock, allowing you to play games from other regi= ons</li> <li>HOME Menu customization, using community-created <a href=3D"https://t= hemeplaza.art/" target=3D"_blank">themes and badges</a></li> <li>Modification of games (=E2=80=9CROM hacks=E2=80=9D) through <a href= =3D"https://github.com/knight-ryu12/godmode9-layeredfs-usage/wiki/Using-Lum= a3DS'-layeredfs-(Only-version-8.0-and-higher)" target=3D"_blank">LayeredFS<= /a></li> <li>Save data editing, backup, and restore</li> <li>Emulation of older consoles, as well as native playback of DS and GBA= games</li> <li>Installing your physical cartridges for digital use</li> </ul> <h2 id=3D"what-does-this-guide-install">What does this guide install?<a cla= ss=3D"header-link" href=3D"https://3ds.hacks.guide/#what-does-this-guide-in= stall" title=3D"Permalink"><span class=3D"sr-only">Permalink</span><i class= =3D"fas fa-link"></i></a></h2> <p>This guide will:</p> <ul> <li>Install <strong>boot9strap</strong> and <strong>Luma3DS custom firmwa= re</strong> on unmodified retail 3DS/2DS devices <ul> <li>Luma3DS will automatically remove the region lock and allow you t= o run unsigned software</li> </ul> </li> <li>Install various pieces of homebrew software, such as a package instal= ler, save file manager, and a homebrew app store</li> <li>Make critical system file backups that can help avoid bricks (and rec= over data in the event of one)</li> </ul> <h2 id=3D"what-do-i-need-to-know-before-starting">What do I need to know be= fore starting?<a class=3D"header-link" href=3D"https://3ds.hacks.guide/#wha= t-do-i-need-to-know-before-starting" title=3D"Permalink"><span class=3D"sr-= only">Permalink</span><i class=3D"fas fa-link"></i></a></h2> <ul> <li>It=E2=80=99s actually really easy to hack your 3DS. Anyone can do it.= </li> <li>While the risks of bricking have been minimized over the years, <stro= ng>we are not responsible for anything that goes wrong with your device</st= rong>. Incorrect file placement will not brick your device, but reckless be= havior might.</li> <li>This guide is compatible with every retail device in the Nintendo 3DS= family of consoles (including the New 3DS series and the 2DS), regardless = of region or firmware.</li> <li>While we believe that custom firmware is safe for online use, there h= ave been online network bans in the past, primarily for cheating and suspic= ious eShop behavior.</li> <li>Following this guide alone should not result in data loss, but SD car= d corruption is always a possibility. You should make a backup of your SD c= ard contents if you have important data.</li> <li>You will need a working SD card in your 3DS, as well as the ability t= o write files to the SD card. The 3DS can read SD cards formatted as MBR/FA= T32. <ul> <li>You may want to check your SD card for errors using <a href=3D"ht= tps://3ds.hacks.guide/h2testw-(windows)">H2testw (Windows)</a>, <a href=3D"= https://3ds.hacks.guide/f3-(linux)">F3 (Linux)</a>, or <a href=3D"https://3= ds.hacks.guide/f3xswift-(mac)">F3XSwift (Mac)</a>.</li> </ul> </li> <li>If you are using Windows to move files to/from the SD card, you may w= ant to <a href=3D"https://3ds.hacks.guide/file-extensions-(windows)">enable= file extensions</a> to avoid misnaming files.</li> </ul> <hr> <h3 class=3D"notice--primary" id=3D"continue-to-get-started">Continue to <a= href=3D"https://3ds.hacks.guide/get-started">Get Started</a><a class=3D"he= ader-link" href=3D"https://3ds.hacks.guide/#continue-to-get-started" title=
